Let f:\mathcal {M}\mapsto \mathbb {R} be smooth on the Riemannian manifold \mathcal {M} . The Riemannian gradient \,\operatorname {grad}f(\boldsymbol {x})\, of f at \boldsymbol {x}\in \mathcal {M} is the unique tangent vector at \boldsymbol {x} such that
